quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
30,6,"This is Allah's promise and He does not go back on His promise. But most people do not know."
30,7,"People simply know the outward aspect of the worldly life but are utterly heedless {1} of the Hereafter.",footnotes:1:That is
30,8,"Do they not reflect on themselves? {1} Allah created the heavens and the earth and whatever lies between them in Truth and for an appointed term. {2} Yet many people deny that they will meet their Lord. {3}",footnotes:1:(2) He has been life free to choose a way of life for himself. He can follow the way of belief or disbelief
30,9,"Have they not travelled through the earth that they may observe what was the end of their predecessors {1} who were far mightier and tilled the land {2} and built upon it more than these have ever built? {3} And Allah's Messengers came to them with Clear Signs. {4} It was not Allah Who wronged them, but it is they who wronged themselves. {5}",footnotes:1:This is a historical argument for the Hereafter. It means this: The Hereafter has not been denied only by a couple of the people in the world
30,10,"Evil was the end of those evil-doers, for they gave the lie to Allah's Signs and scoffed at them."
30,11,"Allah creates in the first instance and will later repeat it. {1} Thereafter it is to Him that you shall be sent back.",footnotes:1:Though this thing has been put forward as a claim
30,12,"On that Day when the Hour will come to pass, {1} the criminals shall be dumbfounded. {2}",footnotes:1:“The Hour”: the Hour of returning to Allah and appearing before Him.|180179:The word ubliso in the text means to be dumbfounded on account of a sudden shock and despair
30,13,"None whom they had associated with Allah in His Divinity will intercede on their behalf; {1} rather, they will disown those whom they had set up as Allah's associates in His Divinity. {2}",footnotes:1:“Associates” (shuraka) includes three kinds of beings:|180181:(1) The angels
30,14,"On that Day when the Hour will come to pass, people will be split into groups. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
30,15,"Then those who believed and acted righteously will be placed in a Garden {1} and will be happy and jubilant. {2}",footnotes:1:“A Garden”: A garden of bliss and perfect happiness as a reward and source of everlasting joy.|180184:The word yuhbarun in the original implies this: “They will be lodged in it with honor
